 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Distributive Fluvial System Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "## Purpose\n",
    "Multi-scale statistical analysis of distributive fluvial systems using manual digitisation data. This notebook processes channel geometry, environmental distributions, and downstream trends for individual DFS systems.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Analysis Framework\n",
    "1. **Profile Analysis**: LOWESS smoothing for channel gradient calculation\n",
    "2. **Downstream Trend Analysis**: OLS regression for width measurements (R², p-value, CV)\n",
    "3. **Multi-Scale Environmental Analysis**: System/Domain/Reach scale environmental distributions\n",
    "\n",
    "## System Selection\n",
    "Modify the system parameters below to analyse any of the five study systems:\n",
    "- `rio_fragua_chorroso` (Tropical, Colombia)\n",
    "- `canning_river` (Polar, Alaska)\n",
    "- `nabesna_river` (Continental, Alaska)\n",
    "- `brahmaputra_river` (Subtropical, India)\n",
    "- `unnamed_iranian_dfs` (Drylands, Iran)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# SYSTEM CONFIGURATION - MODIFY FOR DIFFERENT SYSTEMS\n",
    "# =====================================================\n",
    "\n",
    "# Change these parameters for different systems\n",
    "SYSTEM_NAME = \"rio_fragua_chorroso\"  # Options: rio_fragua_chorroso, canning_river, nabesna_river, brahmaputra_river, unnamed_iranian_dfs\n",
    "SYSTEM_DISPLAY_NAME = \"Río Fragua Chorroso\"\n",
    "CLIMATE_ZONE = \"Tropical\"\n",
    "LOCATION = \"Colombia\"\n",
    "SYSTEM_LENGTH_KM = 30.0\n",
    "\n",
    "# Data file path (standardised naming)\n",
    "DATA_FILE = f\"../data/{SYSTEM_NAME}_analysis_data.xlsx\"\n",
    "\n",
    "# Output directory\n",
    "OUTPUT_DIR = f\"../results/system-outputs/{SYSTEM_NAME}/\"\n",
    "\n",
    "# Special parameters (adjust based on system)\n",
    "DRY_RIVERBED = False  # Set True for unnamed_iranian_dfs only\n",
    "ARCTIC_SYSTEM = False  # Set True for canning_river and nabesna_river\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Analysis configured for: {SYSTEM_DISPLAY_NAME} ({CLIMATE_ZONE}, {LOCATION})\")\n",
    "print(f\"Data file: {DATA_FILE}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Output directory: {OUTPUT_DIR}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# IMPORT PACKAGES\n",
    "import scienceplots\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import statsmodels.api as sm\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from moepy import lowess\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "import warnings\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Configure plotting style\n",
    "plt.style.use(['science','ieee'])\n",
    "plt.rcParams['figure.dpi'] = 300\n",
    "plt.rcParams['savefig.dpi'] = 300\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create output directory\n",
    "output_path = Path(OUTPUT_DIR)\n",
    "output_path.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Libraries imported and output directory created: {output_path}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Channel Profile Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "LOWESS regression analysis of elevation profiles to smooth noise and calculate channel gradients."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# LOAD LONG PROFILE DATA\n",
    "lonPro = pd.read_excel(DATA_FILE, sheet_name='channel_profile')\n",
    "print(f\"Loaded channel profile data: {len(lonPro)} points\")\n",
    "display(lonPro.head())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# LOWESS PROFILE ANALYSIS\n",
    "# SELECT VARIABLES\n",
    "x = lonPro['distance_km'].values\n",
    "y = lonPro['elevation_m'].values\n",
    "\n",
    "# MODEL FITTING\n",
    "lowess_model = lowess.Lowess()\n",
    "lowess_model.fit(x, y)\n",
    "\n",
    "# MODEL PREDICTION\n",
    "x_pred = np.linspace(x.min(), x.max(), 30) \n",
    "y_pred = lowess_model.predict(x_pred)\n",
    "\n",
    "# PLOTTING\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
    "plt.plot(lonPro['distance_km'], lonPro['elevation_m'], label='Raw Data', color='#1F77B4')\n",
    "plt.plot(x_pred, y_pred, '-', label='LOWESS', color='#FF7F0E', zorder=6, linewidth=2)\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Distance (km)\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Elevation (m)\")\n",
    "plt.title(f\"{SYSTEM_DISPLAY_NAME} - Channel Longitudinal Profile\")\n",
    "plt.margins(0.05, 0.1)\n",
    "plt.legend(frameon=True)\n",
    "plt.grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n",
    "\n",
    "# SAVE AND DISPLAY PLOT\n",
    "profile_file = output_path / f\"{SYSTEM_NAME}_channel_profile.svg\"\n",
    "plt.savefig(profile_file, format='svg', dpi=300, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "print(f\"Profile plot saved: {profile_file}\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# CALCULATE SLOPE METRICS\n",
    "x1 = lonPro['distance_km'].iloc[0] * 1000  # Convert to metres\n",
    "y1 = lonPro['elevation_m'].iloc[0]\n",
    "\n",
    "xLast = lonPro['distance_km'].iloc[-1] * 1000\n",
    "yLast = lonPro['elevation_m'].iloc[-1]\n",
    "\n",
    "slope = (yLast - y1) / (xLast - x1)\n",
    "total_relief = y1 - yLast\n",
    "avg_gradient = total_relief / (lonPro['distance_km'].iloc[-1])\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Channel Profile Metrics for {SYSTEM_DISPLAY_NAME}:\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Overall slope: {slope:.6f} m/m ({abs(slope):.6f} absolute)\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Total relief: {total_relief:.1f} m\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Average gradient: {avg_gradient:.2f} m/km\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Profile length: {lonPro['distance_km'].iloc[-1]:.1f} km\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Cross-Section Scale Width Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "OLS regression analysis of channel belt and active channel width trends with statistical significance testing."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# LOAD CROSS-SECTION DATASET\n",
    "river = pd.read_excel(DATA_FILE, sheet_name='cross_section_scale')\n",
    "print(f\"Loaded cross-section data: {len(river)} measurements\")\n",
    "display(river.head())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# DOWNSTREAM WIDTH TRENDS - OLS REGRESSION\n",
    "# Determine column names based on system type\n",
    "if DRY_RIVERBED:\n",
    "    active_channel_col = 'dry_riverbed'  # For Iranian system\n",
    "    active_channel_label = 'Dry Riverbed'\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    active_channel_col = 'wetted_channel'  # For all other systems\n",
    "    active_channel_label = 'Wetted Channel'\n",
    "\n",
    "# Find line of best fit\n",
    "a, b = np.polyfit(river['segment'], river['channel_belt'], 1)  # Channel belt trend\n",
    "c, d = np.polyfit(river['segment'], river[active_channel_col], 1)  # Active channel trend\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create width trends plot\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
    "\n",
    "with plt.style.context(['science', 'nature']):\n",
    "    # Add data points\n",
    "    ax.scatter(river['segment'], river['channel_belt'], color='#000000', label='Channel Belt', s=50)\n",
    "    ax.scatter(river['segment'], river[active_channel_col], color='#1F77B4', label=active_channel_label, s=50)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Add lines of best fit\n",
    "    ax.plot(river['segment'], a*river['segment']+b, color='#dc0500ff', linewidth=2, linestyle='--')  # Channel belt\n",
    "    ax.plot(river['segment'], c*river['segment']+d, color='#FF7F0E', linewidth=2, linestyle='--')  # Active channel\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Customise plot\n",
    "    ax.set_xlabel('% total distance')\n",
    "    ax.set_ylabel('Width (km)')\n",
    "    ax.set_title(f'{SYSTEM_DISPLAY_NAME} - Channel Width Downstream Trends')\n",
    "    ax.margins(0.05, 0.2)\n",
    "    ax.legend()\n",
    "    ax.grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n",
    "\n",
    "# SAVE AND DISPLAY PLOT\n",
    "width_file = output_path / f\"{SYSTEM_NAME}_width_trends.svg\"\n",
    "plt.savefig(width_file, format='svg', dpi=300, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "print(f\"Width trends plot saved: {width_file}\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# OLS STATISTICAL ANALYSIS - CHANNEL BELT WIDTH\n",
    "y_belt = river['channel_belt']\n",
    "x_belt = river['segment']\n",
    "\n",
    "# Add constant to predictor variables\n",
    "x_belt_const = sm.add_constant(x_belt)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Fit linear regression model\n",
    "model_belt = sm.OLS(y_belt, x_belt_const).fit()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Extract statistics\n",
    "belt_r2 = model_belt.rsquared\n",
    "belt_p = model_belt.pvalues[1]  # p-value for slope (exclude intercept)\n",
    "belt_cv = (y_belt.std() / y_belt.mean()) * 100  # Coefficient of variation\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"CHANNEL BELT WIDTH STATISTICS:\")\n",
    "print(f\"R² = {belt_r2:.3f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"p-value = {belt_p:.3f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"CV = {belt_cv:.1f}%\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nFull OLS Summary:\")\n",
    "print(model_belt.summary())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# OLS STATISTICAL ANALYSIS - ACTIVE CHANNEL WIDTH\n",
    "y_active = river[active_channel_col]\n",
    "x_active = river['segment']\n",
    "\n",
    "# Add constant to predictor variables\n",
    "x_active_const = sm.add_constant(x_active)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Fit linear regression model\n",
    "model_active = sm.OLS(y_active, x_active_const).fit()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Extract statistics\n",
    "active_r2 = model_active.rsquared\n",
    "active_p = model_active.pvalues[1]  # p-value for slope\n",
    "active_cv = (y_active.std() / y_active.mean()) * 100  # Coefficient of variation\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"{active_channel_label.upper()} WIDTH STATISTICS:\")\n",
    "print(f\"R² = {active_r2:.3f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"p-value = {active_p:.3f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"CV = {active_cv:.1f}%\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nFull OLS Summary:\")\n",
    "print(model_active.summary())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Cross-Section Scale Environmental Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "Analysis of environmental distributions using cross-section measurements with both absolute areas and normalised proportions."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Cross-section environmental analysis (wetted channel vs bar complex)\n",
    "# Determine column names based on system type\n",
    "if DRY_RIVERBED:\n",
    "    water_col = 'dry_riverbed'\n",
    "    water_label = 'Dry Riverbed'\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    water_col = 'wetted_channel'\n",
    "    water_label = 'Wetted Channel'\n",
    "\n",
    "# CREATE PLOT FOR WATER vs BAR COMPLEX (absolute widths)\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
    "river.plot(x=\"segment\",\n",
    "           y=[water_col, 'bar_complex'],\n",
    "           kind=\"bar\",\n",
    "           stacked=True,\n",
    "           color=['#4477aa', '#ee8866'],\n",
    "           ax=ax)\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel(\"% total distance\")\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel(\"Width (km)\")\n",
    "ax.set_title(f\"{SYSTEM_DISPLAY_NAME} - Cross-Section Environmental Widths\")\n",
    "ax.margins(0.05, 0.19)\n",
    "ax.legend([water_label, 'Bar Complex'])\n",
    "ax.grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n",
    "\n",
    "# SAVE AND DISPLAY PLOT\n",
    "env_width_file = output_path / f\"{SYSTEM_NAME}_environmental_widths.svg\"\n",
    "plt.savefig(env_width_file, format='svg', dpi=300, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "print(f\"Environmental widths plot saved: {env_width_file}\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# CREATE NORMALISED PROPORTIONS\n",
    "riverCopy_1 = river.copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "# CONVERT ROW VALUES TO PERCENTAGES\n",
    "riverCopy_1[[water_col, 'bar_complex']] = riverCopy_1[[water_col, 'bar_complex']].apply(lambda x: x/x.sum(), axis=1).multiply(100)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Normalised environmental proportions:\")\n",
    "display(riverCopy_1[[water_col, 'bar_complex']].head())\n",
    "\n",
    "# CREATE NORMALISED PLOT\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
    "riverCopy_1.plot(x=\"segment\",\n",
    "                 y=[water_col, 'bar_complex'],\n",
    "                 kind=\"bar\",\n",
    "                 stacked=True,\n",
    "                 color=['#4477aa', '#ee8866'],\n",
    "                 ax=ax)\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel(\"% total distance\")\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel(\"Width normalised (%)\")\n",
    "ax.set_title(f\"{SYSTEM_DISPLAY_NAME} - Cross-Section Environmental Proportions\")\n",
    "ax.legend([water_label, 'Bar Complex'])\n",
    "ax.grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n",
    "\n",
    "# SAVE AND DISPLAY PLOT\n",
    "env_prop_file = output_path / f\"{SYSTEM_NAME}_environmental_proportions.svg\"\n",
    "plt.savefig(env_prop_file, format='svg', dpi=300, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "print(f\"Environmental proportions plot saved: {env_prop_file}\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# OLS REGRESSION - BAR COMPLEX DOWNSTREAM TRENDS\n",
    "# Find line of best fit for bar complex\n",
    "a, b = np.polyfit(river['segment'], river['bar_complex'], 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))\n",
    "with plt.style.context(['science', 'nature']):\n",
    "    # Add points to plot\n",
    "    ax.scatter(river['segment'], river['bar_complex'], color='#ee8866', s=50)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Add line of best fit to plot\n",
    "    ax.plot(river['segment'], a*river['segment']+b, color='#FF7F0E', linewidth=2, linestyle='--')\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Add axis labels\n",
    "    ax.set_xlabel('% total distance')\n",
    "    ax.set_ylabel('Bar Complex Width (km)')\n",
    "    ax.set_title(f'{SYSTEM_DISPLAY_NAME} - Bar Complex Downstream Trend')\n",
    "    ax.margins(0.05, 0.2)\n",
    "    ax.grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n",
    "    \n",
    "# SAVE AND DISPLAY PLOT\n",
    "bar_trend_file = output_path / f\"{SYSTEM_NAME}_bar_complex_trend.svg\"\n",
    "plt.savefig(bar_trend_file, format='svg', dpi=300, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "print(f\"Bar complex trend plot saved: {bar_trend_file}\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# OLS MODEL SUMMARY FOR BAR COMPLEX\n",
    "y = river['bar_complex']\n",
    "x = river['segment']\n",
    "\n",
    "# Add constant to predictor variables\n",
    "x = sm.add_constant(x)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Fit linear regression model\n",
    "model = sm.OLS(y, x).fit()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Extract key statistics\n",
    "bar_r2 = model.rsquared\n",
    "bar_p = model.pvalues[1]  # p-value for slope\n",
    "bar_cv = (y.std() / y.mean()) * 100\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"BAR COMPLEX STATISTICS:\")\n",
    "print(f\"R² = {bar_r2:.3f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"p-value = {bar_p:.3f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"CV = {bar_cv:.1f}%\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nFull OLS Summary:\")\n",
    "print(model.summary())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Detailed Environmental Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "Analysis of individual environment types (wetted channel, vegetated bars, unvegetated bars) with downstream trends."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
